{"comments":"Keyframe data for motion graphics animation.\n\nA keyframe represents a specific value at a specific point in time.\nThe interpolation between keyframes is controlled by tangent handles\nand interpolation type.\n\n## Keyframe Structure\n\n```\n    ┌───┐ in tangent\n    │   │\n────●───────●────  value\n        │   │\n        └───┘ out tangent\n    frame\n```\n\n## Interpolation Types\n\n- **Linear**: Straight line between keyframes\n- **Bezier**: Smooth curve controlled by tangent handles\n- **Hold**: Value stays constant until next keyframe\n- **Auto**: System calculates smooth tangents automatically\n\n## Usage\n\n```purescript\nimport Hydrogen.Schema.Motion.Keyframe as KF\nimport Hydrogen.Schema.Dimension.Temporal (frames)\n\n-- Create a numeric keyframe\nkf = KF.keyframe (frames 30.0) (KF.NumberValue 100.0)\n\n-- With bezier easing\nkfEased = KF.withBezierTangents (KF.tangent 0.0 0.0) (KF.tangent 0.3 0.0) kf\n\n-- Create position keyframe\nposKf = KF.keyframe (frames 0.0) (KF.Vec2Value { x: 100.0, y: 200.0 })\n```\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["id",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Motion","Keyframe"],"KeyframeId"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["frame",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Dimension","Temporal"],"Frames"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["value",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Motion","Keyframe"],"KeyframeValue"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["interpolation",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Motion","Keyframe"],"InterpolationType"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["inTangent",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Motion","Keyframe"],"Tangent"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["ou